The paper deals with the problem of power scheduling in multi-access transmission, which is a common issue in wireless sensor networks. The approach is based on information theory and optimization, which are typical topics in the cs.IT (Information Theory) and cs.SY (Systems and Control) sub-categories. The paper also discusses the application of the proposed method to wireless sensor networks, which falls under the cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) sub-category. Additionally, the paper involves the use of convex optimization, which is a common technique in the cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) sub-category. Finally, the paper deals with scheduling and allocation problems, which are relevant to the cs.MA (Multi-Agent Systems) sub-category.
